    <fr:title text="Forester 4.0 › enhanced XML support › emitting XML and resolving namespaces › XML literals"><fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-00RJ.xml" title="Forester 4.0 › enhanced XML support › emitting XML and resolving namespaces" addr="forest://forester/jms-00RJ" type="local"><fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-00RH.xml" title="Forester 4.0 › enhanced XML support" addr="forest://forester/jms-00RH" type="local"><fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-00RF.xml" title="Forester 4.0" addr="forest://forester/jms-00RF" type="local">Forester 4.0</fr:link> › enhanced XML support</fr:link> › emitting XML and resolving namespaces</fr:link> › XML literals</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Feature</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>The old <html:code><![CDATA[\xml]]></html:code> syntax has been replaced with a new convenient notation for XML literals that supports <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-00RK.xml" title="Forester 4.0 › enhanced XML support › emitting XML and resolving namespaces › XML namespace declaration" addr="forest://forester/jms-00RK" type="local">declared XML namespace prefixes</fr:link>. The grammar of XML literals is summarised below:</html:p>
    <html:pre><![CDATA[qname ::= prefix:name | name
expr ::= ... | \<qname>[qname]{expr}...{expr}]]></html:pre>
    <html:p>For example, if the prefix <html:code>html:</html:code> is bound to <fr:link href="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" type="external">http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml</fr:link> as in <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/forester/jms-00RK.xml" title="Forester 4.0 › enhanced XML support › emitting XML and resolving namespaces › XML namespace declaration" addr="forest://forester/jms-00RK" type="local">Feature <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://forester/jms-00RK" /></fr:link>, the expression <html:code><![CDATA[\<html:mark>[class]{highlight}{some highlighted text}]]></html:code> will emit the following XML:</html:p>
    <html:pre><![CDATA[<html:mark
  xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  class="highlight">
 some highlighted text
</html:mark>]]></html:pre>
    <html:p>In reality, the appropriate <html:code>@xmlns:html</html:code> attribute will be attached only where it is needed in keeping with the hierarchical structure of the XML tree. Note that when the same textual prefix is bound to two different namespaces, one of them will be automatically <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex>-renamed so as to result in correct XML with the intended semantics.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
